# Workspace build before commit

**Rule:** Before committing, run `cargo build` at the **workspace root** (`agents/backend/`), not only a single crate. Stale incremental caches can hide cross-crate type errors.

## Why

`cargo build -p <crate>` only checks the dependency graph for that crate. If a shared dependency (e.g. `common`, `api`) changes but a dependent crate has not been recompiled yet, the single-crate build can succeed using stale artifacts and hide type mismatches.

**Modules:** Orphaned source files (present on disk but not `mod` in the crate root) are not compiled. Verify wiring with `rg "mod your_module" path/to/crate` before assuming a build covers them.

## Commands

| Scenario | Command |
|----------|---------|
| Before commit | `cd agents/backend && cargo build` |
| Quick check (single crate) | `cd agents/backend && cargo build -p <crate>` |
| After changing shared types (`common`, `api`, `broker_engine`) | `cd agents/backend && cargo build` (full workspace) |

## Anti-pattern

```bash
# Wrong — single crate can miss cross-crate errors
cargo build -p backend_service && git commit

# Correct — workspace build
cd agents/backend && cargo build && git commit
```

**Parity:** Same policy as `.opencode/rules/workspace-build-before-commit.md` (OpenCode).
